      <originalsloc id="aspace_f86e3d5cb74ab2e09a929803cbb49a14">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection is available on microfilm (HM 262) and in the Lewis W. Fairchild Papers (MS 921).   The papers consist of letters from Alvin J. Johnson, publisher in New York of bibles, atlases and encyclopedias, to Lewis W. Fairchild concerning the sale of books in Fairchild's territory. The remainder of the papers consists of letters and weekly reports on sales to Fairchild and Johnson from their agents and canvassers in Connecticut, Massachusetts and New York. Also included are Fairchild's personal bills (1884-1888). These papers were formerly known as the Alvin J. Johnson Papers.</p>  
      </originalsloc>
